ZH: 我们每周都要进行一次口试。
EN: We have an oral test every week.

ZH: 明天的口试将涵盖词汇和语法。
EN: Tomorrow's oral test will cover vocabulary and grammar.

ZH: 我们需要准备好口试材料。
EN: We need to prepare for the oral test.

ZH: 这次口试的内容很难。
EN: The content of this oral test is difficult.

ZH: 我很紧张，因为我不擅长口试。
EN: I'm nervous because I'm not good at oral tests.

ZH: 你可以和同学一起练习口试。
EN: You can practice the oral test with your classmates.

ZH: 老师要求每个学生都参加口试。
EN: The teacher requires every student to participate in the oral test.

ZH: 我需要提高我的口试成绩。
EN: I need to improve my oral test score.

ZH: 我们的口试成绩将影响最终成绩。
EN: Our oral test scores will affect our final grades.

ZH: 她的口试表现非常出色。
EN: Her performance on the oral test was excellent.

ZH: 昨天的口试很容易。
EN: Yesterday's oral test was easy.

ZH: 我们需要注意口试的时间限制。
EN: We need to pay attention to the time limit for the oral test.

ZH: 我们可以通过多练习来提高口试表现。
EN: We can improve our performance on the oral test through practice.

ZH: 参加口试需要大声说出答案。
EN: Participating in the oral test requires speaking out the answers loudly.

ZH: 我总是在口试时紧张。
EN: I always get nervous during oral tests.

ZH: 完成口试后，我们会得到反馈。
EN: After completing the oral test, we will receive feedback.

ZH: 我们必须独立完成口试。
EN: We must complete the oral test independently.

ZH: 口试是考察口语能力的重要途径。
EN: The oral test is an important way to assess oral skills.

ZH: 参加口试让我更自信了。
EN: Participating in the oral test made me more confident.

ZH: 我们将在周五进行口试。
EN: We will have the oral test on Friday.
